{
    "identity": "nprot-36",
    "title": "<em>Candida albicans</em> infection",
    "content": [
        {
            "header": "Introduction",
            "content": "This is a protocol to induce disseminated candidiasis in mice. _Candida albicans_ infection experiments were performed as previously described with minor modifications \\(_Blood._ 2000 Jun 15; **95\\(12)**:3725-3733)."
        },
        {
            "header": "Reagents",
            "content": "Reagents:\r\n\n\n_Candida albicans_ \\(ATCC 18804).\r\n\n\nSabroud Dextrose Broth \\(Sigma Aldrich, St Louis, MO).\r\n\n\nSterile phosphate buffered saline \\(PBS), room temperature."
        },
        {
            "header": "Equipment",
            "content": "1 ml syringe.\r\n\n\n27-gauge needle.\r\n\n\n14 ml round bottom conical tube with snap cap.\r\n\n\nHemocytometer."
        },
        {
            "header": "Procedure",
            "content": "1. Make a frozen stock of subcultures of _Candida albicans_ at -80\u00b0C in Sabroud Dextrose Broth containing 15% glycerol.\r\n  2. Plate cultures on Sabouraud dextrose agar plates and grow at 37 \u00b0C for 24 hours. The plates can be stored at 4 \u00b0C for a maximum of 4 weeks.\r\n  3. Before each experiment, pick a colony from a plate and grow in 5 ml of Sabouraud Dextrose Broth in a 14 ml conical tube at 37 \u00b0C for 24 hours in a shaker.\r\n  4. Centrifuge the cells \\(1000 rpm for 5 minutes) and wash the pellet twice with 5 ml of sterile PBS and resuspend in PBS.\r\n  5. Count the cell number using a hemocytometer, and then adjust to the desired concentration.\r\n  6. Inject 2-5 \u00d7 10\n5\ncolony-forming units of _C albicans_ dissolved in 200 \u03bcl of sterile PBS from tail vein to induce disseminated candidiasis."
        },
        {
            "header": "References",
            "content": "Basu S _et al. Blood._ 2000 Jun 15; **95\\(12)**:3725-3733"
        }
    ],
